Please note: Travel advice for the territory of American Samoa will now be included in our travel advice page for the USA. This page will be removed from GOV.UK shortly. If you have subscribed to receive email alerts for American Samoa, you will no longer receive updates. If you wish to continue to receive updates relating to American Samoa, you will need to subscribe to our USA travel advice.
If you’re abroad and you need emergency help from the UK government, contact the nearest British embassy, consulate or high commission.
Although there’s no recent history of terrorism in American Samoa, attacks can’t be ruled out. See Terrorism
Most visits to American Samoa are trouble-free.
Take out comprehensive travel and medical insurance before you travel.
